# v0.5.13 Change Log

**Theme**: Phase 4 — coordinator-api bounded context formalization, JWT library standardization, and codebase cleanup.

**Goal**: Standardize both services on a single JWT library (PyJWT), audit and document cross-context boundary violations in coordinator-api, add context documentation, decide the agent-coordinator service boundary, and clean up lint/infra issues discovered during the audit.

**Context**: v0.5.12 completed duplication elimination and large-file decomposition (B1–B7). v0.5.13 kicks off Phase 4 — formalizing the bounded-context architecture in coordinator-api. The initial Phase 4 draft contained factual errors (rate limiter no-op claim, wrong file counts, wrong auth file locations) that were corrected before execution.

**Status**: Fully implemented. All 5 Phase 4 tasks (P1–P5) complete, plus 2 cleanup items (E501, secrets.baseline), plus P2-followup orphan audit, P2-followup-2 pricing_models revival, T1 Tier 1 migrations (6 models), T2 Tier 2 shared-kernel migrations (2 models), and T3 Tier 3 boundary-violation migrations (2 models + 1 documented).

