**Problem**: 38 imports across 10 contexts reach into the flat `app/domain/` instead of their own `contexts/<bc>/domain/`. Many carry `# type: ignore[import-not-found]`.

**Fix**: Produced <ref_file file="/opt/aitbc/docs/releases/v0.5.13/context_import_audit.md" /> (267 lines) cataloguing all 38 cross-references with categorization:

| Category | Count | Description |
|----------|-------|-------------|
| (a) Intra-context | 20 | Model belongs to importing context — migrate file + fix import path |
| (b) Shared kernel | 9 | Model genuinely shared by 2+ contexts — keep as shared kernel or extract |
| (c) Boundary violation | 9 | Context reaches into another context's domain — needs service interface |

**Key findings**:
- 3 models already migrated with correct `..domain.*` relative imports: `global_marketplace` (10 refs), `gpu_marketplace` (5 refs), `agent_identity` (1 ref) — all in `marketplace` and `agent_identity` contexts
